message: Healthcare slavery ... Me: middle class, 62, 1 knee replacement,1 going, 2 kids. Got a quote earlier in the year were I to retire $2000 a month...you heard me 2 grand a month. It would be more then my social security benefit. Now they say it's going up by double digits. $2400?, $2600, $2800... Does it matter? It simply isn't feasible. So we are like many and the many that will soon discover they can't retire. We are health insurance slaves - we work to fund other people health insurance.
